{
  "texts": [
    "It does not imply that the data will always be available.",
    "The fundamental design of Blockchain architecture prioritizes data availability over data retrievability.",
    "A small number of archive nodes managed by outside parties may offer data retrievability, or decentralized file repository systems like the Portal Network can be used to spread data around the network 62.",
    "We have considered four parameters such as reliability, accuracy, throughput, and communication overhead to measure the execution of the preferred performance.",
    "The level of Reliability of a network refers to its ability to be deemed trustworthy, consistent, and dependable."
  ]
}